Subject: [PATCH 7/7] pager: Fix ansi chars not being stripped correctly

MaybeStripAnsi wasn't correctly applied to text streams, meaning that
when called with `LESS=-c PAGER=less` (ie LESS is defined but doesn't
include `-R`) the ansi chars should be stripped but weren't.

This fixes the problem by ensuring text streams get unwrapped and
re-wrapped in a MaybeStripAnsi object (and also get flushed correctly
when handling KeyboardInterrupt)
